<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5793/3</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hongkong</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tredwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hongkong</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-22"><hi rend="italic">September 22,
                                    1925</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received October 26.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 24</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith copy
                            of a communication received to-day from the Colonial Secretary of the
                            Colonial Government of Hongkong,<note n="78" xml:id="d183fn78">Not
                                printed.</note> in which I am informed that His Excellency the
                            Governor has withdrawn the provisional recognition which was accorded to
                            Mr. H. C. Anderson, Assistant Customs Attaché, at this port.<note n="79" xml:id="d183fn79">The consul in charge at Hongkong had been
                                instructed on May 5 to notify the local authorities of the
                                appointment of Mr. Anderson as assistant customs attaché at Hongkong
                                (file No. 121.5793/a).</note></p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Roger Culver
                            Tredwell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>